# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
# Everything (HTML pages included) must revalidate on every load so deploys
# reach returning visitors immediately — a stale cached page paired with fresh
# JS (or vice versa) renders broken sections until a hard refresh. ETag keeps
# revalidation cheap: unchanged files return a 304, not the full body.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

# Heavy media: detach the /* revalidate rule so Cloudflare Pages' default
# asset policy applies instead (observed live: public, max-age=14400,
# must-revalidate — 4 h of browser cache, then cheap ETag 304s). Note the
# explicit week-long Cache-Control set after ! was ignored by the parser;
# the default is close enough, so we document reality rather than fight it.
/images/*
  ! Cache-Control

/videos/*
  ! Cache-Control
